==Swedish==
===Suffix===
'''-is'''
*[[Wiktionary:Swedish pronunciation|Pronunciation]]: when combined the stress is always on the first syllable
#(''colloquial, particularly common in the Stockholm area'') suffix that gives a familiar, and to some extent a [[diminutive]] nuance, when combined with a word; common with both [[noun]]s and [[adjective]]s: ''brådis, funkis, sotis''; commonly used for place names, institutions and persons in their professional role'': [[:w:Medborgarplatsen|Medis]], [[:w:Salvation Army|frälsis]], [[dagis]], [[vaktis]]''
#:''Är du '''sotis''' över att hon träffar sina killkompisar på krogen?''
#::"Are you jealous about her seeing her male friends at the pub?"
#:''Hämta '''vaktisen'''. Någon hade just sönder en fönsterruta.''
#::"Get the janitor. Someone just broke a window."
#(''colloquial'') in ad hoc combinations: ''[[pannkaka|pankis]], sötis, snuskis''
#:''Kan vi inte äta '''pankisar''' med sylt och grädde idag?''
#::"Can we eat pancakes with jam and (whipped) cream today?"
#:''Du får inte hoppa över kontroller på orienteringen, din '''fuskis'''!''
#::"You can skip orienteering controls, you cheater!"

====Etymologi====
At least since the late 1880s. Originally from the Latin ending ''-is'' in words like ''[[basis]]'' "basis".

